// @test regression/break-continue-outside-loop
// @description break/continue parse as a bare Identifier statement; outside any loop they are TV's CE10135/CE10136 ("... is only allowed inside loops."). Inside a for/while body - including nested inside an if within the loop - they stay clean (loopDepth, not blockDepth, gates this). Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv, see INV092.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=3, message=/"break" is only allowed inside loops/
// @expects error: line=4, message=/"continue" is only allowed inside loops/
// @expects errors: 2

//@version=6
indicator("break-continue-outside-loop")
break
continue
for i = 0 to 3
    if i > 1
        break
    else
        continue
while close > open
    break
plot(close)
